title: Tea Caddy And Cover / Wrong Number?, 1875–1900
markings: Marks: On bottom, in underglaze blue: "A P K"
provenance: Greenwood and Clark (Antiques) Dorchedter-on-Thame, Oxford, England Phelps Warren (1961)
description: Rectangular body with champfered corners; straight-sided circular neck, flat-topped cover; painted in underglaze blue on white on 2 sides with fig-ures, on the shorter sides with reserves of sailboats on floral pattern background, floral band around top body; cover painted with floral motifs.
